# Project AI Assistant Notes

This is a JUCE standalone macOS app built with CMake (no Projucer).
It answers Universal Device Inquiry as a Matrix-1000 or Matrix-6 (provisional) over MIDI.

## Layout

- `Source/` — application sources (`Main.cpp`, `DeviceInquiry.h`, …).
- `Assets/Icons/` — app icon PNG (macOS Dock via `ICON_BIG` in CMake).
- `Docs/` — long-term project knowledge (PascalCase, like `Source/` and `Builds/`).
- `CMakeLists.txt` — build configuration; register new `.cpp` files in `target_sources`.
- `CMakeUserPresets.json` — per-platform CMake presets (Debug / Release).

## Build

JUCE is located via the `JUCE_DIR` environment variable, per-OS paths in `CMakeLists.txt`, or a standard install path. Configure and build with the preset for your platform, for example:

`cmake --preset macos-debug-arm64 && cmake --build --preset macos-debug-arm64`

See `README.md` for usage and protocol notes.

## Conventions

- Target the C++ standard set in `CMakeLists.txt` (`CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD` — currently C++20).
- Version SSOT: `project(Matrix-Simulator VERSION …)` in CMake.
- Refer to the JUCE 8 API: https://docs.juce.com
- Cursor agent rules: `.cursor/rules/` (authoritative for communication, process, and coding standards).
